arolingian period witnessed a remarkable adaptability among these women. Through texts, objects, archaeological remains, and iconography, Dark Age Nunneries offers scholars of religion, medieval history, and gender studies new ways to understand the experience of women of faith within the Church and across society during this era.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aConventszEuropexHistoryyTo 1500. 0aMonastic and religious life of womenzEuropexHistoryyMiddle Ages, 600-1500. 0aMonasticism and religious orders for womenzEuropexHistoryyMiddle Ages, 600-1500. 0aMonasticism and religious orders for womenzEuropexHistoryyMiddleAges, 600-1500. 4aMedieval & Renaissance Studies. 4aReligious Studies. 4aWomens Studies.  awoman's monasticism, medieval history, lotharingia, gender, reform.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060655308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2018 Englishz978311060403008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2018z9783110603149oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501715976?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501715976423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501715976/original  a978-3-11-060403-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060655-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb